name as a prefix.

buttonVisibleIdentify Organism:
For each sequence, BLASTs it against a database, copying the organism property from the top hit
to the query sequence as long as it meets minimum similarity requirements.

To view the results, select 'Show Organism' in the General section of the Sequence View controls.

Note: For large data sets you should use the Classify Sequences plugin
or for 16S data, 16S Biodiversity from the Tools menu.

buttonVisibleCombined mapping and de novo assembly:
Maps some paired reads to a a reference sequence. Takes all those reads along
with their mates and de novo assembles them. Iterates 2 more times. And maps
the final de novo assembly contigs back to the reference sequence.

buttonVisibleFree End Gaps Alignment:Whether or not this alignment is considered to have free end gaps. Free end gaps are not rendered and do not contribute towards statistics nor the similarity graph.

buttonVisibleMerge mapped sequences:Given a contig which contains some sequences mapped to a reference sequence, extracts a list of
sequences mapped with overlapping sequences merged together.

Overlapping sequences with disagreements are merged using default consensus calling options, which
uses highest quality calling when quality information is available.

This operation is not suitable for merging 100,000 or more sequences. It is intended for
genome finishing by merging a few mapped contigs produced from a de novo assembly.

buttonVisibleSet CDS Translation Property:
Adds a "Translation" annotation to each CDS annotation.
The genetic code specified by the transl_table qualifier is used.
Otherwise, uses the genetic code specified for the document.
Otherwise, uses the default genetic code from cog icon in sequence viewer translation options.
